{
  "texts": [
    "However, to the best of our knowledge, there are very few studies that comprehensively explore the explainability of social media recommendations from the end user's perspective, such as why end users possibly require explainable content recommendations on social media, how the recommendations can be presented and their possible impact on users.",
    "An exploratory analysis of explainable social media recommendations can shed light on users' explanation perception, attributes of explanation, and its effect on end users.",
    "Additionally, for practitioners to develop an explainable social media recommendation platform, it is crucial to understand the end user requirements, the explanation format, and the feasibility of explainable systems (Bunde, 2021).",
    "The above discussion shows that end user-oriented explainable recommendations in social media are a relatively underexplored area in XAI research and hence advocate further exploration (Haque et al., 2023; Laato et al., 2022).",
    "Therefore, in this work, we focus on AI-based content suggestions on Facebook, a popular social media platform, to explore the end users' notion regarding the explainability of the recommendation system."
  ]
}